---
By: Seneca
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 135
    Verse: 6
Tags:
  - Evil
---
There is no evil that does not offer inducements. Avarice promises money;
luxury, a varied assortment of pleasure; ambition, a purple robe and
applause. Vices tempt you by the rewards which they offer.
